#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""dp-brief — parse DP/Inner Circle AM Call transcriptions into structured trading briefs.

Usage:
  dp-brief              — read from stdin (paste transcription, Ctrl+D to finish)
  dp-brief --file FILE  — read from file
  dp-brief --json       — machine-readable JSON output

Extracts:
  - Market bias and outlook
  - DP's current positions (SHORT/LONG/SOLD/FLAT)
  - Key levels (resistance, support, 21-day MA)
  - Analyst upgrades/downgrades/price targets
  - Catalysts and upcoming events

Handles Dropbox speech-to-text errors:
  - "queues"/"the Qs" -> QQQ, "GE Vinova" -> GEV, "58463" -> 584.63
  - Missing decimals in prices, garbled ticker names

Reference: DP.md — David Prince's trading methodology (conviction mapping,
  sizing rules, key MAs, language-to-signal mapping)

Environment:
  No dependencies — stdlib Python only.
"""

